I need you to go somewhere urgently.

148
00:09:39,210 --> 00:09:40,410
Sure, where?

149
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,340
I need you to go to Hong Kong
and look into something.

150
00:09:43,610 --> 00:09:45,450
Take an afternoon flight tomorrow.

151
00:09:45,510 --> 00:09:46,680
No problem, ma'am.

152
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,480
Get some rest.

153
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:11,240
Did you sort things out with the helper?

154
00:10:11,570 --> 00:10:14,610
Jun-mo apologized to her in person,
and they agreed to settle.

155
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:18,950
So you agreed to pay her for physical
and psychological damage too, right?

156
00:10:19,010 --> 00:10:20,510
You heard him say the matter is settled.

157
00:10:21,580 --> 00:10:22,750
Then...

158
00:10:26,290 --> 00:10:28,160
[Petition for Expulsion
Under the Code of Decency]

159
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,690
How do you explain this?

160
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:31,460
[Petition for Expulsion
Under the Code of Decency]

161
00:10:31,530 --> 00:10:34,400
Jae-in's mom volunteered to collect
the signatures. Didn't you know?

162
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:37,370
No, I had no idea that you two were close.

163
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:42,040
I suppose you thought you could
shake me up with this piece of paper.

164
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:45,540
I don't care if you bad-mouth me
or collect signatures to kick me out.

165
00:10:45,970 --> 00:10:49,680
But do you enjoy blackmailing
powerless people to do things like this?

166
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,080
Is it how you show off your power?

167
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:53,710
-What?
-Jae-in's mom volunteered to help?

168
00:10:54,050 --> 00:10:55,820
I bet she was left with no choice.

169
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:01,590
Whether you believe me or not
is entirely your choice,

170
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:03,420
but you still don't seem to know

171
