263
00:17:45,590 --> 00:17:48,700
There's going to be a music festival soon.

264
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:51,570
Yes, Si-woo.

265
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:53,230
What's that, Ms. Kim?

266
00:17:53,330 --> 00:17:56,540
It's an orchestra show,
and we'll perform as well.

267
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:59,940
So we'll start practicing from today.

268
00:18:00,070 --> 00:18:03,540
Have you all decided on the instrument
you prefer to play?

269
00:18:03,610 --> 00:18:05,450
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

270
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:07,150
Jae-in, you picked the violin.

271
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:08,780
-Can you show me?
-Sure.

272
00:18:21,230 --> 00:18:22,800
-They're so good.
-Amazing.

273
00:18:23,430 --> 00:18:25,630
-Gosh, they're really good.
-Is this a violin battle?

274
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:29,270
She's so good.

275
00:18:33,740 --> 00:18:36,440
Wow, Jun-hee and Jae-in.

276
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:39,810
Both of you have
very impressive violin skills.

277
00:18:40,050 --> 00:18:42,450
I can even play more difficult ones.

278
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:45,050
Great. Very impressive.

279
00:18:48,820 --> 00:18:51,930
Yi-chan,
any instrument that you want to play?

280
00:18:53,390 --> 00:18:55,000
Okay, then...

281
00:18:57,460 --> 00:18:59,200
Let's go with this.

282
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:01,140
Okay.

283
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:04,000
Hold it. And try it like that.

284
00:19:06,670 --> 00:19:08,210
Great. Very good.

285
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:53,050
Teacher Danny!

286
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:54,660
Hey, Jae-in.

287
00:19:55,660 --> 00:20:00,060
So, I lost my phone on Camp Day.

288
00:20:00,130 --> 00:20:01,430
Have you seen it?

289
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:02,830
Your phone?

290
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:08,670
-Is it this one?
-Yes!

291
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:09,770
Wait.

292
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:13,740
Is this really yours, Jae-in?

293
00:20:15,740 --> 00:20:16,810
It is.

294
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:19,950
It's okay. You can tell me.

295
00:20:20,380 --> 00:20:22,180
-Actually,
-Yes?

296
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:26,550
it belongs to Yi-chan.

297
00:20:29,590 --> 00:20:32,690
Then how about this?

298
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:36,130
I'll return it to the actual owner.

299
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:39,200
I won't tell him you had it.

300
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:44,870
Can you really do that?

301
00:20:45,170 --> 00:20:47,940
Mom told me not to tell anyone.

302
00:20:48,010 --> 00:20:50,080
Yes, I promise.

303
00:20:50,140 --> 00:20:52,210
You have to keep it a secret.

304
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:54,110
Especially from An Yi-chan.

305
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:58,450
-Pinky promise.
-Okay, pinky promise.

306
00:21:02,620 --> 00:21:05,760
Jae-in, do you know
how to play "Chopsticks"?

307
00:21:06,260 --> 00:21:08,230
Then how about we play it together?

308
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:14,430
Let's see how good you are at the piano.

309
00:21:14,670 --> 00:21:16,170
Are you ready?

310
00:21:16,970 --> 00:21:19,070
One, two, three, start.

311
00:21:51,670 --> 00:21:53,840
[Locanda Jeju Hotels and Resorts
Legendary Pool Members Only]

312
00:21:53,910 --> 00:21:55,280
-I want to eat fruits.
-This is nice.

313
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:57,010
-Let's make a toast.
-Okay.

314
00:21:57,840 --> 00:21:59,750
-Cheers!
-I love it here.

315
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:02,720
Hello.

316
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:08,490
What brings you all the way here?

317
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:12,290
Well, since you're here, drink up.

318
00:22:12,390 --> 00:22:15,430
Here. Congratulations, Ms. Song.

319
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:18,000
Please take good care of us from now on.

320
00:22:19,370 --> 00:22:21,270
There's no need for that.

321
00:22:21,870 --> 00:22:24,570
By the way, I didn't know you came first.

322
00:22:27,980 --> 00:22:30,210
Jun-hee's mom got in touch first,

323
00:22:30,280 --> 00:22:32,210
but I wasn't sure if you were free.

324
00:22:33,510 --> 00:22:35,180
I see.

325
00:22:36,580 --> 00:22:38,750
It's nice to have everyone here.

326
00:22:39,050 --> 00:22:41,390
-Let's hang out often.
-That'd be great.

327
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:43,090
Yes.

328
00:22:43,290 --> 00:22:46,060
We've been a bit unfriendly so far.

329
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:50,360
Well, we can all
get to know each other from now on.

330
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:53,470
I hope we get along.

331
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:56,140
-Let's toast. Cheers!
-Cheers!

332
00:22:58,540 --> 00:23:02,140
That reminds me,
it's the kids' music festival soon.

333
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:04,210
I heard practice started on Monday.

334
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:06,710
Noah is playing the cello.

335
00:23:07,150 --> 00:23:10,650
-Yu-bin is playing the violin.
-Jae-in is playing the violin too.

336
00:23:12,950 --> 00:23:14,220
What about Yi-chan?

337
00:23:14,990 --> 00:23:16,790
The orchestra never crossed our minds.

338
00:23:16,860 --> 00:23:19,160
But he doesn't know
how to play any instruments.

339
00:23:19,390 --> 00:23:21,030
So he's in charge of the cymbals.

340
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:24,530
The cymbals?
My Si-woo is playing the drums.

341
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:28,570
I took him to famous music classes
ever since he was little

342
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:31,470
and taught him all sorts of instruments
from piano and flute to violin.

343
00:23:31,540 --> 00:23:34,710
But he's just not good at classical music.

344
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:37,540
So I'm thinking of teaching him
the drums later on.

345
00:23:37,610 --> 00:23:39,810
He's not that bad at hitting things.

346
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:43,050
Starting music lessons at a young age

347
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:46,920
is a compulsory subject
in teaching them humanism.

348
00:23:47,050 --> 00:23:51,220
Their concentration and endurance will
improve if they stick to it. Right?

349
00:23:51,290 --> 00:23:52,560
Right, concentration.

350
00:23:54,060 --> 00:23:55,460
And also,

351
00:23:55,560 --> 00:24:00,700
grade one is going to make the opening
speech at this year's festival.

352
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:03,270
That's going to be cute!

353
00:24:03,700 --> 00:24:06,440
Hold on.
Is Jun-hee going to make the speech?

354
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:10,280
Not alone.

355
00:24:11,410 --> 00:24:12,980
It's a duo...

356
00:24:14,510 --> 00:24:15,620
with Jae-in.

357
00:24:20,290 --> 00:24:23,120
Jae-in's mom
brought her daughter up really well.

358
00:24:23,190 --> 00:24:25,730
She's got a long way
to catch up to Jun-hee.

359
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:29,530
What's this, Jae-in's mom?
Is this how you're going to push through?

360
00:24:30,130 --> 00:24:31,630
It's not like that.

361
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:35,140
Excuse me for a minute.

362
00:24:46,150 --> 00:24:47,250
What's going on?

363
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:00,960
[Women]

364
00:25:01,430 --> 00:25:03,360
Thank you for keeping your word.

365
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:05,300
What's going on between you
and Yi-chan's mom?

366
00:25:05,370 --> 00:25:07,100
You two seemed close.

367
00:25:08,140 --> 00:25:09,240
I'm not sure.

368
00:25:10,370 --> 00:25:12,140
But I don't have friends to begin with.

369
00:25:13,170 --> 00:25:14,240
How interesting.

370
00:25:14,510 --> 00:25:16,810
It's none of my business,

371
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:18,950
but this is all I can do to help you.

372
00:25:19,010 --> 00:25:20,710
The rest is up to you.

373
00:25:22,420 --> 00:25:25,650
But you know what'll happen

374
00:25:26,390 --> 00:25:28,190
if you drag Jun-hee down.

375
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:30,120
Don't worry. That will never happen.

376
00:26:05,690 --> 00:26:07,990
-Shall we have another round of drinks?
-Sure!

377
00:26:08,090 --> 00:26:10,200
We're all going
for the second round, right?

378
00:26:10,860 --> 00:26:12,300
Where's Yi-chan's mom?

379
00:26:12,370 --> 00:26:14,940
She wasn't feeling well,
so she left not too long ago.

380
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,500
I'm glad she knows when to butt out.

381
00:26:24,710 --> 00:26:26,080
Why are you leaving already?

382
00:26:27,210 --> 00:26:29,380
I forgot Jae-in has a lesson today.

383
00:26:30,020 --> 00:26:31,790
I'll get going first.

384
00:26:35,790 --> 00:26:40,730
Anyway, gives us some details
about what's going on, Ji-seon.

385
00:26:40,790 --> 00:26:43,760
What's with Jae-in's mom all of a sudden?
What are you planning?

386
00:26:44,030 --> 00:26:46,100
There's a saying.

387
00:26:46,630 --> 00:26:49,400
Use your enemy's hand to catch a snake.

388
00:26:49,470 --> 00:26:52,940
So you're going to use
your enemy's hands to catch a snake?

389
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:56,610
We'll have to see
if she's an enemy or an ally.

390
00:26:58,110 --> 00:27:00,480
You've been bringing out
rats, cats, and snakes since last time.

391
00:27:00,550 --> 00:27:02,280
This isn't some kind of zoo!

392
00:27:02,350 --> 00:27:04,020
Use words I can understand.

393
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:06,820
I'm already stressed out by
all the English at the kids' school.

394
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:08,890
Seriously.

395
00:27:10,160 --> 00:27:11,630
One more glass!

396
00:27:11,690 --> 00:27:15,760
Really. I should've studied English.

397
00:27:52,900 --> 00:27:53,970
Ms. Song!

398
00:27:55,970 --> 00:27:57,470
My gosh, Chef Jung.

399
00:27:58,770 --> 00:28:00,610
I'm surprised to run into you here.

400
00:28:03,980 --> 00:28:05,780
-Right.
-What brings you here?

401
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:08,820
I'm here with the other moms.

402
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:12,320
You never called. I'm glad to see you.

403
00:28:12,490 --> 00:28:15,220
Oh, I'm sorry. I was meaning to drop by,

404
00:28:15,290 --> 00:28:16,660
but I've been too busy.

405
00:28:17,690 --> 00:28:21,060
Speaking of which, how about right now?

406
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:24,330
Right now?

407
00:28:31,870 --> 00:28:33,570
Thank you for this.

408
00:28:34,540 --> 00:28:37,740
Like I said, I've been looking forward
to treating you.

409
00:28:48,190 --> 00:28:51,060
It was a year ago today, right?
Your anniversary.

410
00:28:59,330 --> 00:29:02,740
Montrachet.
It's a Chardonnay from Burgundy.

411
00:29:04,740 --> 00:29:06,340
It was Mr. An's favorite.

412
00:29:06,610 --> 00:29:09,640
In France, they call it
the wine of paradise.

413
00:29:10,140 --> 00:29:13,350
It's perfect for this kind of
weather and season.

414
00:29:27,990 --> 00:29:29,400
You remember everything.

415
00:29:30,060 --> 00:29:33,730
I assumed you needed to talk
to somebody on a day like this.

416
00:29:34,100 --> 00:29:35,840
I apologize if I made you uncomfortable.

417
00:29:37,470 --> 00:29:38,570
Not at all.

418
00:29:39,810 --> 00:29:42,980
It's just that I don't know what to do.

419
00:29:43,810 --> 00:29:46,780
I can neither remember him nor forget him.

420
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:50,120
I can't believe it's already been a year.

421
00:29:58,930 --> 00:30:01,430
-Were you that hungry?
-Yes.

422
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:04,000
That dress was suffocating me.

423
00:30:04,730 --> 00:30:05,900
I can finally breathe now.

424
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:10,100
Congratulations on your anniversary.

425
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,240
Thank you.

426
00:30:12,710 --> 00:30:14,340
How do you like the food?

427
00:30:14,410 --> 00:30:16,240
It couldn't be more perfect.

428
00:30:16,510 --> 00:30:18,510
What about you?
We haven't dined here in a while.

429
00:30:18,580 --> 00:30:21,280
I'm trying to savor every bite.

430
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:22,950
Thank you, Mr. Jung.

431
00:30:23,420 --> 00:30:25,590
Please let me know
if you need anything more.

432
00:30:25,650 --> 00:30:26,790
We will.

433
00:30:28,690 --> 00:30:30,860
We haven't done this in so long.
I want to do this properly.

434
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:32,090
Let's clink glasses.

435
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:43,870
Honey. This isn't the end.

436
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:48,040
[That was our last dinner together.]

437
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:51,950
Come to think of it,

438
00:30:52,810 --> 00:30:54,880
he barely touched his dinner that day.

439
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:56,750
But I didn't notice it.

440
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:02,760
I'm sorry I'm being all gloomy
in front of food.

441
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:04,690
Don't worry.

442
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:08,130
By the way,

443
00:31:08,830 --> 00:31:12,830
I'm not sure if I should tell you this
after all this time,

444
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:15,070
but it's about Mr. An.

445
00:31:15,770 --> 00:31:19,510
I saw him with someone that day
before you came.

446
00:31:20,310 --> 00:31:21,640
He was with someone?

447
00:31:22,010 --> 00:31:23,640
Are you kidding me?

448
00:31:23,810 --> 00:31:25,810
This doesn't make any sense!

449
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:28,580
Are you serious?

450
00:31:28,650 --> 00:31:30,320
You can't go back on your word now.

451
00:31:31,750 --> 00:31:35,260
I couldn't see the face well,
but I think it was a woman.

452
00:31:36,060 --> 00:31:37,190
A woman?

453
00:31:38,090 --> 00:31:40,590
The atmosphere was quite heavy.

454
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:43,600
You didn't seem to know about it,

455
00:31:43,660 --> 00:31:45,800
so I kept quiet.

456
00:31:46,070 --> 00:31:49,840
But I had a feeling that I should tell you
even if it's too late.

457
00:31:51,270 --> 00:31:52,410
I see.

458
00:31:54,040 --> 00:31:55,580
Thank you for telling me.

459
00:32:00,250 --> 00:32:07,150
[Salon de Ae]

460
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:07,420
Thank you again.

461
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:08,890
I really enjoyed the food.

462
00:32:09,260 --> 00:32:11,760
See you again.
Next time, how about dinner?

463
00:32:11,820 --> 00:32:12,960
Sounds good.

464
00:32:14,760 --> 00:32:17,960
[Salon de Ae]

465
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:23,300
[Salon de Ae]

466
00:32:32,310 --> 00:32:34,210
Sweetheart. When did you get here?

467
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:38,820
I came to see you,
but the two of you seemed so lovey-dovey.

468
00:32:39,690 --> 00:32:40,990
Come on, it wasn't like that.

469
00:32:41,050 --> 00:32:42,590
What's going on between you two?

470
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:44,290
Why were you with her alone at this hour?

471
00:32:45,090 --> 00:32:46,930
I just treated her to a meal.

472
00:32:47,830 --> 00:32:49,230
Just a meal?

473
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:51,730
She was my regular in Seoul.

474
00:32:51,830 --> 00:32:54,270
Now that we met here again,
I couldn't pretend we were strangers.

475
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:58,870
Hold on.
Don't tell me you're suspecting me.

476
00:32:58,940 --> 00:33:00,270
It was just a meal.

477
00:33:00,340 --> 00:33:01,740
How can I be sure

478
00:33:01,810 --> 00:33:03,910
whether it was just a meal
or there was something more?

479
00:33:04,710 --> 00:33:05,710
What?

480
00:33:08,350 --> 00:33:11,550
Then explain what this is.

481
00:33:13,750 --> 00:33:15,460
You dropped it.

482
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:19,760
It's ready. What do you think?

483
00:33:19,830 --> 00:33:21,130
It looks great.

484
00:33:22,130 --> 00:33:23,400
One more thing.

485
00:33:23,930 --> 00:33:26,800
Can you send this with the flowers?

486
00:33:27,730 --> 00:33:30,700
Sure. Can you give me
your name and phone number?

487
00:33:30,770 --> 00:33:35,310
Well, I want to surprise my girlfriend.

488
00:33:35,410 --> 00:33:37,480
Can you send it without my name?

489
00:33:38,540 --> 00:33:40,410
Sure. I'll do that.

490
00:33:40,810 --> 00:33:42,650
You're so romantic.

491
00:33:43,650 --> 00:33:46,520
Don't tell anyone that I was here.

492
00:33:51,660 --> 00:33:53,090
Is this what this is all about?

493
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:55,090
It was to a client.

494
00:33:55,430 --> 00:33:58,360
You never give me any presents.
Why would you send flowers to anyone?

495
00:33:59,830 --> 00:34:02,170
Why are you being like this?

496
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:05,370
I'm right here. I'm not going anywhere.

497
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:08,440
-Isn't that enough?
-Why Song Yeo-wool, of all people?

498
00:34:08,570 --> 00:34:11,510
She left early saying she wasn't
feeling well. So what was she doing here?

499
00:34:11,580 --> 00:34:13,610
I get it. That's enough.

500
00:34:14,050 --> 00:34:15,820
This is a waste of time.

501
00:34:15,980 --> 00:34:18,120
Didn't you say you were busy
with your kid's school events?

502
00:34:18,420 --> 00:34:21,120
Goodness. You seem busier than me.

503
00:34:21,190 --> 00:34:22,520
Busy having meals with another woman.

504
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:26,389
That's enough. Stop now, okay?

505
00:34:32,030 --> 00:34:33,370
Okay.

506
00:34:33,770 --> 00:34:35,070
I'm hungry.

507
00:34:36,469 --> 00:34:39,270
Isn't there something
more urgent than that?

508
00:34:40,370 --> 00:34:41,570
My goodness.

509
00:34:43,239 --> 00:34:45,340
Hold on. My back.

510
00:35:31,990 --> 00:35:33,230
[Missed call from Danny Oh]

511
00:35:32,890 --> 00:35:34,930
How about 9 p.m. on Wednesdays?

512
00:35:35,530 --> 00:35:38,160
-Sure.
-Let's start next week.

513
00:35:39,470 --> 00:35:41,230
Right, that's today.

514
00:35:45,200 --> 00:35:48,240
[Danny Oh]

515
00:36:13,430 --> 00:36:15,840
Mr. Oh, I'm sorry.

516
00:36:15,900 --> 00:36:18,540
I was busy all day,
and it slipped my mind.

517
00:36:31,750 --> 00:36:33,190
I'm so sorry.

518
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:37,660
You showed up 50 minutes late,
and the student isn't even here.

519
00:36:38,490 --> 00:36:40,460
He's failing from his first lesson.

520
00:36:40,690 --> 00:36:42,900
I'm sorry you had to wait so long.

521
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:44,330
I was just practicing.

522
00:36:44,700 --> 00:36:46,330
We can have the lesson another day.

523
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:51,140
Take this.

524
00:36:53,710 --> 00:36:55,580
Oh, my. How do you have this?

